Surf-machine2_remix_v1 ______________________ Look my other submissions Here! - Keep in mind that this is an early preview of the v1 a new v2 will follow with a lot more features! - This map was originally made by Z-machine and was reloaded by me! - Map can host 32 players / same as original. - Map has cystom skybox and all new textures that stand out from the old machine2. - The jail system has changed a bit from the original, there are three buttons ( Red ) ( Yellow ) ( Green ) - The red button activates a env_steam wich makes a heat wave and kills the players. - The yellow button opens the jail door 7 seconds after it has been pressed. - The green button opens the door immediately. - Some ideas were taken from surf_triangle and surf_machine_remix_v2 by Paper- Cut. - I have added very much props in the map, and although this is just an aplha i think it has nearly no bugs. - I have also remove all old edges and added smooth corners and edges on all possible surface. - And please rate the map after you play it and not accordingly of the images as they do not show the whole map and the stuff it has got. - I placed a monitor on the Z-top ich you can see the jail in. - Custom weapon dispencers. - Melons replaced with oranges xD - All textures replaced with new - 60 % smoother ramp - Many places to honour Z-machine - + A "Pro" way - The proway can be found on top of the Z-top there it is a round teleport wich leads you to an easy outdoor skill surf for the newbies at surf. - Time spent on map this far: 6 hours + 10 min compile - Map has been majorly optimized since it has got many more planes after the smooth edges and these stuff. - 4 hudhints - Map automaticly sets the sv_airaccelerate to 150 Enjoy & Have fun! To come to the first sky, fly through the "u" of the Just Chill Wallpaper behind the big "Z".

The teleporter to the 2. sky is behind the rail , where the automatic shotguns are.
You have to fly around this rail, and jump into the back of this rail.

To come to the Secret HeadAdmin Room, where a JetPack and some other cool things are, go into PRE and shoot in the green button of the TOP-Portal.
Then use the secret door at the left.
The 2. door by the secret rooms will open after a few seconds.
There you have to use a key to open the door.
The key is 5487.
To come out of the room shoot the white next to the door!

To come out of the jail, shoot the ball into the white corner!


Have Fun and enjoy this map!

[nyro's SDK Steam Group](http://steamcommunity.com/groups/nyrosdk "nyro's SDK Steam Group") SURF\_LT\_UNICORN - 02-02-15 ======================= - Map by: Nicholas P. Low, aka nyro - Contact: nyronic@gmail.com -
Surf Timer Notes: ------------------ - If your servers plugin does not support filter entities for zone triggers, bonus 1 will most likely NOT work! - Bonus 4 relies on a filtered zone trigger to accurately record completion times, as noted above it's important that your plugin supports filters. If not, the bonus will still function but completion times will be much faster than intended. - Pre-speed prevention should be disabled on stages 2-6, and bonus 4. Otherwise stage linking will not work, and bonus 4 will not work. Other Notes: ------------------ - The rubiks cube at the end was tested with a noblock plugin which sets the player's collision to debris. There were never any issues even with several players standing on it. If the cube is breaking due to players blocking it during rotation, it may be due to the server's noblock plugin. - **FIXED, SEE BELOW**: 100 tick servers will break the cube no matter what, I didn't know about this as I tested on my own PC at the default 66 tick rate. Minor Update - 02-07-15: ------------------ - Fixed the rubiks cube for 100 tick servers with an ent update, the client's bsp will **NOT** differ. For any server admins that care about something silly and pointless, just re-download the map from here! - If you wish to fix it yourself for whatever reason, just find the 3 momentary_rot_button entities, and change their speed value from 360 to 540. That's it, you're done! :) point_servercommand: - sv_enablebunnyhopping 1 - sv_airaccelerate 150 - mp_limitteams 0 - sv_maxvelocity 10000 - mp_freezetime 0 - mp_round_restart_delay 0 Description: - 6 stages increasing in difficulty as you progress. - 4 additional bonus stages. - All surf ramps were made out of models. - Designed for 66 tick. - Support for HDR! SURF_LORE by Target Practice

- This map is a sectioned skill surf.
- There are 7 levels to complete, with an additional 2 bonus levels, and 3 jails.
- Find the secrets and beat the map.
- Each section contains a seperate and unique theme/texture scheme. Custom textures are included.

_________________________________________________


THE MAP

... Upon spawning, you have 5 minutes to complete the map. Should you fail to complete within the timelimit you will be taken to jail 1. If you complete the map within the timelimit, you will be rewarded in jail 2. If you enter a secret code, you can enable Jail 3.


FALLBACK SYSTEM

... For each time you fail to complete a level, 5hp will be taken from your health. If your health gets too low then you have the option to fall back by pressing the red button to return to the previous level. How much will you sacrifice to stay alive?


JAIL 1

... When the timer runs out, you are taken to a jail where you recieve a specific gun depending upon how far you get in the map.

For example: If you reach level 5 when the timer runs out, you will recieve an m4. If you only reach level 2, then you will recieve just a deagle. etc.

Players must battle it out in a gg/fy 2fort style mini map and kill the opposing team before their time runs out.

JAIL 2

... Upon completing the map within the timelimit you will be rewarded with a second jail for easy kills.

JAIL 3

... It's a surprise.

BONUSES

... Complete the 2 bonus sections to recieve special rewards.

_________________________________________________

- Many thanks go to DragonRock and Solidsurf.
- Special thanks go to Buck Nasty for the skybox. Apologies for lack of such credit in the map.
- Further thanks to the original author of the 'toon' textures from cs1.6, and to FAJ for advice and inspiration.
- I appreciate the critisisms and ideas throughout the making of this map.
- Thankyou to the entire DragonRock Clan and Community, and specifically Nelioneil.

I'll admit it right from the start.

This map was a simple 5-10min make, you can be the judge of how good it is for yourself. It's not anything special, by far, rather than a quickie challenge me and a friend made with each other to see who could make a better crap surf map.

Apparently he liked mine, thus, the map is being put out in public just for the hell of it. It's not that it's too short or too simple, it's that it's actually pretty fun.

I'll sum everything up by asking you to check out the screenshots and check it out for yourself. This map has various traps to make it worth wanting to stay alive, though none of them are so hazardous that you continuously fail to survive.

So, Bananites, What do you think?
